comments: Brunson (NYK) legally contests Caruso's (CHI) jump shot attempt.
Green (CHI) reaches in and initiates contact to Brunson's (NYK) arm which affects his driving shot attempt.
Vucevic (CHI) establishes himself in Anunoby's (NYK) path and does not deliver illegal contact.

Hart (NYK) contests the shot and some contact occurs with White (CHI) head and arm during the driving shot attempt.  Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
DiVincenzo (NYK) establishes himself in Caruso's (CHI) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Hartenstein (NYK) legally contests Vucevic's (CHI) jump shot attempt.
Caruso (CHI) makes hand-on-ball contact and cleanly dislodges the ball away from Brunson (NYK).
Anunoby (NYK) legally contests DeRozan's (CHI) jump shot attempt.
DeRozan (CHI) does not overtly or abruptly extend his leg out as incidental contact occurs with Anunoby (NYK) during the jump shot attempt.
Caruso (CHI) legally contests Brunson's (NYK) jump shot attempt.
Caruso (CHI) makes hand-on-ball contact and dislodges the ball away from Brunson (NYK) as he is dribbling on the perimeter.

After the steal, Caruso (CHI) is in control of the ball when Anunoby (NYK) engage in incidental contact with him in an attempt to further tie up the ball. The jump ball is whistled prior to granting Caruso (CHI) a timeout. The shot clock is set to :21 seconds in recognition of Caruso having gained control.
DeRozan (CHI) makes makes marginal contact with Brunson's (NYK) chest while defending the drive.
Caruso (CHI) brushes Brunson's (NYK) arm and marginal contact occurs during Brunson's driving shot attempt.
DiVincenzo (NYK) contests White's (CHI) jump shot and the contact after the release, and follow-through, is marginal.
After the ball becomes loose, DiVincenzo (NYK) initiates contact to White's (CHI) arm and dislodges him from his position.
Caruso (CHI) is absorbing the initial contact that occurs with Anunoby (NYK) and incidental contact occurs as Anunoby (NYK) attempts to move under the pick.
Anunoby (NYK) initiates contact to DeRozan's (CHI) arm during his driving shot attempt.
Green (CHI) makes incidental hand-on-ball contact and blocks the driving shot attempt by DiVincenzo (NYK).
Caruso (CHI) inbounds the ball within five seconds.
Vucevic (CHI) continues to re-establish himself following the initial contact and creates further contact with DiVincenzo (NYK) that affects his ability to defend over the screen.
Caruso (CHI) is last to make contact with the ball before it goes out of bounds. NYK maintains possession of the ball.

call_type: Turnover:  Out of Bounds - Bad Pass Turn
comments: Hart (NYK) does not maintain possession of the ball and is last to make contact before it goes out of bounds.
Achiuwa (NYK) moves alongside DeRozan's (CHI) path and marginal body contact occurs during the driving shot attempt.
Brunson (NYK) and Green (CHI) come together in pursuit of the loose ball during the rebound.
Green (CHI) commits a take foul on Brunson (NYK).
Green (CHI) is last to make contact with the ball before it goes out of bounds NYK maintains possession.
As both Hart (NYK) and Green (CHI) pursue the ball marginal contact occurs while it is airborne.
